physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Elevated thyroid hormone levels and suppressed TSH levels in the absence of thyroid autoantibodies. Thyroid gland of normal size and structure, homogeneous echogenicity, and without hyperperfusion.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: At the age of 11 5/12 years, the thyroid gland remained not enlarged. Blood pressure and heart rate were persistently elevated.
